                        "displayName": "Wes McKinney",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/New_York"
                    },
                    "body": "My understanding is that the safest thing to do in production is use the libhdfs.so that is shipped with a particular Hadoop distribution (since there may be internal details that are particular to that version of Hadoop); while the public C API is the same between versions, in theory there could be internal details in the JNI implementation that break the Java \"ABI\". The Hadoop community would be able to give better advice",
                    "updateAuthor": {
